   =20
      Twitter interest payment
   =20
 =20

Tomorrow seems to be the due date for Twitter Inc.=E2=80=99s first interest=
 payment on the $13 billion it borrowed to fund Elon Musk=E2=80=99s buyout.=
 That=E2=80=99s a little exciting!=C2=A0Will Twitter pay? I mean, probably.=
 Here is a   Bloomberg News article from last week being like =E2=80=9Coh c=
ome on, obviously Elon is gonna pay, Twitter has the money and it=E2=80=99d=
 be crazy not to=E2=80=9D:

By all accounts =E2=80=94 including Elon Musk=E2=80=99s =E2=80=94 Twitter h=
as more than enough money to make its first interest payments, expected to =
total about $300 million. =E2=80=A6
A group of seven banks, led by Morgan Stanley, own the debt. =E2=80=A6 Now,=
 after they lost some $4 billion on paper for backing Musk=E2=80=99s Twitte=
r bid, market onlookers see little reason for the banks to go along with an=
y unexpected maneuvers near the interest-payment deadline, roughly around J=
an. 27.
After all, in most bankruptcies, the equity is wiped out =E2=80=94 and lend=
ers eventually take control.
=E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s too much at stake for Musk and his co-investors,=
=E2=80=9D said Jordan Chalfin, a senior analyst at credit research firm Cre=
ditSights. =E2=80=9CTwitter will make its near-term interest payments, come=
 hell or high water, and give the business time to turn around.=E2=80=9D

